JOHANNESBURG - Tributes have poured in for the former television actress, presenter and Miss Black South Africa Tshegofatso Michelle Molatlou. According to reports, Molatlou "succumbed to her battle with cervical cancer" at the National Hospital in Bloemfontein on Tuesday. The 44-year-old was surrounded by family and friends at the time of her death. Her funeral is set to take place in Bloemfontein on Saturday. Molatlou acted in popular shows like Generations, Kgatelopele and In the Name of Love, before she moved into corporate.  eNCA